records.addlTxt:
Defendant Samuel M Rivera-Nieves in court with attorney Michael L. Chernin.  Kevin R. Shomin on behalf of Erin Karshen appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Deputy court clerk ccp.
Case set for sentencing hearing. Police report made by the defendant received and filed. Statements made as to sentencing.

As to COUNT 4-
Court ordered defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction consecutive to COUNTS 1, 2 & 3; credit for 64 days time served. Court ordered defendant report to the House of Corrections on August 16, 2014 between 8:00 a.m. and 10:00 a.m. Subject to verification by the House of Corrections, Court will allow release for work when called, counseling appointments as ordered by childrens court order, and vocational training classes as needed for employment. 

As to COUNT 1-
Court ordered defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction consecutive COUNTS 2 & 3.

As to COUNT 2-
Court ordered defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction consecutive COUNTS 1 & 3.

As to COUNT 3-
Court ordered defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction consecutive COUNTS 1 & 2.

Court STAYED the sentence on COUNTS 1, 2 & 3 and placed defendant on probation for 2 YEARS.

-Court will allow defendant to earn good time.

-If revoked, court costs, fees and surcharges to be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds. 

-Court will defer ruling on sex offender registration until the review hearing date. 

Conditions of Probation:
1) Cooperate with any orders in the childrens court case 14JC535;
2) No unsupervised contact with children under the age of 16 years, excluding the children living in the residence;
3) No contact with the victim L.T. dob 10/17/2000;
4) Obtain/comply with sex offender evaluation and treatment. Court ordered the case manager in the 14JC535 case to have access to the evaluation results;
5) Pay all costs, fees and surcharges by the end of probation period. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment;
6) Provide DNA sample (unless previously submitted) and pay surcharge;

Filed:
-Sentencing Referral Form;
-Pretrial Incarceration Credit form;
-Notice of Intent to Seek Postconviction Relief.  Review hearing scheduled for August 14, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Arguments heard as to bail. Court ordered cash bail remain at $10,000.00. If the defendant posts bail, he is to be turned over to Justice Point GPS Monitoring. Conditions of monitoring as follows: 
-24 hour curfew;
-Remain in the state of Wisconsin;
-No contact with the victim or any location the victim may be placed;
-No new violations rising to the level of probable cause;
Court will revisit the issue of bail if defense counsel and Justice Point are able to submit on company letterhead of defendant's employer to the Court with the name and phone number of defendant's supervisor, as well as where he will be working and the hours of employment.
